Police are investigating a shooting incident at a popular restaurant in Rosebank, Johannesburg, on Thursday morning. Details are scant at this stage  but Medi Response advanced life support paramedics who responded said a 42-year-old  man was declared dead on the scene. According to Paul Herbst from Medi Response, the man was  having breakfast at  Tashas restaurant  on the outside of The Zone area of the mall when he was accosted by two men. He was shot twice in the head before the perpetrators  fled on foot. Police spokesperson Captain Mavela Masondo said police  were on the scene. This is a developing story TimesLIVE Support independent journalism by subscribing to theÂ Sunday Times. Just R20 for the first month.